reviews.text:
There is quite a good variety of food stalls at this coffeeshop. Some of the popular stalls here are quite good and always have queues forming at their stalls. The three popular stalls here are the caifan, fishball noodle and chicken rice. The pancake stall here is also popular. It is opened in the morning and closes by 2 pm. The crispy pancake is really done well. Very thin and crispy.
There are 2 other coffeeshops in Elias mall but this is the only one with air conditioner.

The food there is getting more and more expensive. The stall selling drinks has a long queue which you even needs to stand outside toilets. The washing bay is so near to the stall with all soap and dirty plates near to the stall serving table. Unhygienic. The tables are always dirty without clean up. I can see there is only 1 person at plates collection counter without any cleaner coming around to clean the tables. No point renovated but yet we can't eat in clean environment.

1st time tried the prawn ball la mian. shiok! Prawny broth very sedap! Umami! Good portion, fresh ingredients,  only $6.80. Way better than ehub prawn noodles. Will.try their hong kong Street zi ca the next time üòÑ
Air-conditioned food court and 2 giant ceiling fans to ventilated the food court. Many stalls. Good numbers of tables and chairs. Its get crowded during lunch time.
WuFu fishball noodles,  Taiwan stall and Hong Geng roast pork stall are great.  They removed the doors 6 Dec, so no longer airconditioned.
